.e. (figuratively) anguish","kjv_def":"agony","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"agony(1x)"},"G82":{"id":"G82","lemma":"ἄδηλος","translit":"ádēlos","derivation":"from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and G1212 (δῆλος);","strongs_def":"hidden, figuratively, indistinct","kjv_def":"appear not, uncertain","pos":"adjective","usage":"uncertain(1x)"},"G50":{"id":"G50","lemma":"ἀγνοέω","translit":"agnoéō","derivation":"from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and G3539 (νοιέω);","strongs_def":"not to know (through lack of information or intelligence); by implication, to ignore (through disinclination)","kjv_def":"(be) ignorant(-ly), not know, not understand, unknown","pos":"verb","usage":"ignorant(4x), ignorantly(2x), unknown(2x)"},"G37":{"id":"G37","lemma":"ἁγιάζω","translit":"hagiázō","derivation":"from G40 (ἅγιος);","strongs_def":"to make holy, i.e. (ceremonially) purify or consecrate; (mentally) to venerate","kjv_def":"hallow, be holy, sanctify","pos":"verb","usage":"sanctify(26x), hallow(2x)"},"G1":{"id":"G1","lemma":"Α","translit":"A","derivation":"of Hebrew origin;","strongs_def":"the first letter of the alphabet; figuratively, only (from its use as a numeral) the first:","kjv_def":"--Alpha","pos":"indeclinable noun","usage":"Alpha(4x)"},"G75":{"id":"G75","lemma":"ἀγωνίζομαι","translit":"agōnízomai","derivation":"from G73 (ἀγών);","strongs_def":"to struggle, literally (to compete for a prize), figuratively (to contend with an adversary), or genitive case (to endeavor to accomplish something)","kjv_def":"fight, labor fervently, strive","pos":"verb","usage":"strive(3x), fight(3x)"},"G31":{"id":"G31","lemma":"ἀγγελία","translit":"angelía","derivation":"from G32 (ἄγγελος);","strongs_def":"an announcement, i.e. (by implication) precept","kjv_def":"message"},"G47":{"id":"G47","lemma":"ἁγνεία","translit":"hagneía","derivation":"from G53 (ἁγνός);","strongs_def":"cleanliness (the quality), i.e. (specially) chastity","kjv_def":"purity"},"G33":{"id":"G33","lemma":"ἄγε","translit":"áge",